  "body": "Most warnings come from third-party plugins (solidity-coverage and gas-reporter). If we update some dependencies in those repos, the warnings will go away.\r\n\r\nAccording to @alcuadrado, this is what we need to do:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsoldity-coverage > detect-port (Upgrade / Vendor as its tiny and pulls deps)\r\nsolidity-coverage > @truffle/provider (Replace)\r\nhardhat-gas-reporter > eth-gas-reporter > mocha (Upgrade)\r\nhardhat-gas-reporter > eth-gas-reporter > request-promise-native (Replace)\r\nhardhat-gas-reporter > eth-gas-reporter > request (Replace)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n\r\neth-gas-reporter package:\r\n- bump ethers version: https://github.com/cgewecke/eth-gas-reporter/pull/296\r\n- request: it seems that the request package is not used, it should be removed: https://github.com/cgewecke/eth-gas-reporter/pull/297\r\n- request-promise-native: https://github.com/cgewecke/eth-gas-reporter/pull/298\r\n\r\nsolidity-coverage:\r\n- update mocha version: [https://github.com/sc-forks/solidity-coverage/pull/810](https://github.com/sc-forks/solidity-coverage/pull/810)\r\n\r\nAfter these changes the packages with the newer and correct versions should be automatically downloaded during the installation. ",
